This sample requires multi-step orchestration (deploy executor → run executor/scripts/setup-a2a.sh → deploy caller) that the standard hosted-agents-cloud-e2e workflow does not support. The caller depends on a Foundry Toolbox (`a2a-delegation-tools`) that is created dynamically by `setup-a2a.sh` against the deployed executor, so a single-step `azd deploy` of the caller would fail when the toolbox lookup hits a nonexistent toolbox. Excluded from the hosted-agents e2e CI pipeline; see README.md for the manual walkthrough.
